@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Home Page";
}

<div class="jumbotron">
    <h1>Student Database List</h1>
    <p class="lead">Basic MVC ASP.NET App for managing a database list of students.</p>
    <p>To run the app, be sure to restore the database located as a backup in the App_Data folder.</p>
    <p>Because two different methods are demonstrated in this app, there two connection strings. They are located at the top of the 
    StudentController and at the bottom of the Web.config file.</p>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h2>Getting started</h2>
        <p>Select "Students" from the navigation bar above.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h2>Basic CRUD Features</h2>
        <p>You may add, view, edit, or remove students from the database.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h2>Methods</h2>
        <p>This app demonstrates both manual ADO.NET tools and the ADO.Net Entity Data Model tools.</p>
        <p>This app also demonstrates the use of separate view models for security purposes.</p>
        <p>This app furthermore utilizes jQuery UI for confirmation of removal from the database.</p>
    </div>
</div>